	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Lancaster</placeName> <date>22 Juny 1857</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
				<p><add>German&#63;</add></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Lancaster</placeName>&#44; <date>June 22&#44; 1857</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Phila</placeName></p>
				<p>Beloved friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have happy news today.  Yesterday&#44; in the morning&#44;<lb/> my wife bore a lusty boy&#8212;&#8212;<add>Hebrew</add>.  The Brith will be on <date>Sunday</date><lb/> morning.  My friend <persName>Newhouse</persName> has been designated as a godfather.<lb/>  I have invited him <sic>tpday</sic> and made it conditional on his bringing<lb/> you with him I want my <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> friends in my house and<lb/> as you are among them <sic>i</sic> request your presence on <date>Sunday</date> with<lb/> <persName>Mr Newhouse</persName> and the <sic>rst</sic> of our friends.  <sic>i</sic> will not accept any<lb/> excuse but count on your presence so that you may help to<lb/> increase the joy of the festival.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">etc etc</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">Signed&#8212;Your sincere friend</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Jacob Herzog</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">I expect you in company with <persName>Mr Bachmann</persName>&#44; <persName>Mr<lb/> Newhouse</persName> and <persName>Mr Spartz</persName>&#44; <persName>Frank S. Cohen</persName></p>
		</body>
